# No Reverts / History Safety

**Purpose:** Prevent accidental resets/rebases/branch switches or pushes to the wrong place.

**Rules (must always be followed):**
- **NEVER** run any of these without explicit confirmation from me:
- `git reset` (any mode), `git rebase` (any form), `git clean`, `git stash pop`,
 `git checkout <commit>` (detached), `git push --force` / `-f`, or deleting branches/remotes.
- **NEVER** switch to or push to **rescue/today** (or any branch other than `main`) unless I say:
**“YES, switch to <branch> and push”**.
- Before any potentially destructive action, you must:
1) Explain exactly what will happen,
2) Show the exact commands you would run,
3) Wait for me to reply **“YES PROCEED”** (exact phrase).  
  If I don’t reply with that exact phrase, **do nothing**.

**Safe defaults:**
- Default branch for all pushes is **main**.
- Default remote is **origin** at  
`https://github.com/mblinch/flofile_clean.git`.*